# Givt App Versioning Rules

- **Always bump the app version when making changes**:
  - When you implement changes that will be merged into `develop`, ensure the app version is increased if it has not already been bumped for this batch of work.
  - The version is defined in the Flutter `pubspec.yaml` for the app; make sure that the version on `develop` is **strictly higher** than the version on `main`.

- **How to choose the new version**:
  - **Patch release (`x.y.(z+1)`)**:
    - Use when changes are **backwards compatible** and relatively small:
      - Bug fixes and regression fixes
      - Minor UI tweaks or copy changes
      - Internal refactors or performance improvements with no user-visible feature changes
  - **Minor release (`x.(y+1).0`)**:
    - Use when changes introduce **new user‑visible behavior**:
      - New features or flows
      - New screens or significant UX changes
      - New analytics events for shipped features
  - **Major release (`(x+1).0.0`)**:
    - **Do not decide automatically.** Major version bumps are handled manually outside this rule and should only happen when explicitly requested.

- **Branch relationship (`main` vs `develop`)**:
  - When starting a new set of changes on `develop`, if the `develop` version **matches** `main`, choose an appropriate bump (patch or minor) and apply it on `develop`.
  - Ensure that, before merging `develop` back into `main`, the `main` branch will move to the **same** (already bumped) version as `develop`, so there is always a clear version difference between releases.

